# GitHubExercise
Git workflow

# **GitHub Exercise**

# 1. Create a Local Repository and Add/Commit Files
mkdir GitHubExercise
cd GitHubExercise
git init
echo "This is my first GitHub exercise." > file1.txt
git add file1.txt
git commit -m "Initial commit with file1.txt"

# 2. Create a Remote Repository and Push Local Repo to Remote
# (Replace <remote-repo-URL> with your actual GitHub repository URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/Gabo0701/GitHubExercise.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

# 3. Create a Local Branch and Add/Commit Files
git branch feature-branch
git checkout feature-branch
echo "This is a feature file for the GitHub exercise." > feature.txt
git add feature.txt
git commit -m "Add feature.txt to feature-branch"

# 4. Push the Local Branch to GitHub (Create a Remote Branch)
git push -u origin feature-branch
